Enum IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus

    IExternalProxy

    public static enum IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus
extends java.lang.Enum<IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus>
    Possible values for the SYNC_STATUS_PROPERTY.

    NOTE: the enum literals must be spelled the same as the the literals for the SyncStatus enumeration in the model. The order doesn't matter, however.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      CONFLICT

      CYCLE

      INCOMING_ERROR
      The last attempt to create or modify a Jazz object has failed for for some reason.
      OK
      The last known state of the external object has been synchronized with the last known state of a Jazz item.
      OUTGOING_ERROR
      The last attempt to create or modify an external object has failed for some reason.
      PENDING
      An operation is known to be pending for the proxy - an incoming or outgoing replication or synchronization operation is expected to occur.
      UNINITIALIZED
      Indicates that no external state has yet been received, and that it is not pending.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • UNINITIALIZED

        public static final IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus UNINITIALIZED
        Indicates that no external state has yet been received, and that it is not pending. This is the default state of a newly-created proxy.

      • OK

        public static final IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus OK
        The last known state of the external object has been synchronized with the last known state of a Jazz item. The #getExternalStateHandle() and #getLastSyncedStateId() methods will return valid values, and no error has occurred.

      • PENDING

        public static final IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus PENDING
        An operation is known to be pending for the proxy - an incoming or outgoing replication or synchronization operation is expected to occur.

      • OUTGOING_ERROR

        public static final IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus OUTGOING_ERROR
        The last attempt to create or modify an external object has failed for some reason. The IExternalProxy.getLastErrorString() method will return any error information that was collected.

      • INCOMING_ERROR

        public static final IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus INCOMING_ERROR
        The last attempt to create or modify a Jazz object has failed for for some reason. The IExternalProxy.getLastErrorString() method will return any error information that was collected.

      • CONFLICT

        public static final IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus CONFLICT
        During either incoming or outgoing synchronization, it was discovered that both the external object and the Jazz item have been modified since they were last synchronized, and those changes are not auto-mergeable.

      • CYCLE

        public static final IExternalProxy.SynchronizationStatus CYCLE
        Too many outgoing/incoming cycles have occurred. Cycles can occur when both Jazz and the external repository modify the new state of an object when it is applied, in such a way that the two states never become equivalent. In order to avoid endless cycles, incoming synchronization is rejected after exceeding the maximum cycle count configured in the synchronization rule.
